<subSubSection pageNumber="301" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="301">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="301">Note:</emphasis>
This name has been treated as illegitimate by some authors (see Milne-Redhead in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="301">Bot. Mag.</emphasis>
160: t. 9510. 1938; de Vos in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="301">J. S. African Bot.</emphasis>
42: 333-334. 1976). However, this does not seem to be the case because Linnaeus did not cite 
<taxonomicName authority="Mill. (1768)" authorityName="Mill." authorityYear="1768" class="Liliopsida" family="Iridaceae" genus="Watsonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="humilis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="301">Watsonia humilis</emphasis>
Mill. (1768)
</taxonomicName>
as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Linnaeus, 1753" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1774" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Iridaceae" genus="Antholyza" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="merianella">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="301">A. merianella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and Miller did not cite his own t. 279, f. 2 (1760) in publishing 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Iridaceae" genus="Watsonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="humilis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="301">W. humilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(while Linnaeus did). Matters are complicated by the existence of the heterotypic 
<taxonomicName authority="Thunb. (1784)" authorityName="Thunb." authorityYear="1784" class="Liliopsida" family="Iridaceae" genus="Gladiolus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="merianellus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="301">Gladiolus merianellus</emphasis>
Thunb. (1784)
</taxonomicName>
- see Roux (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="301">J. S. African Bot.</emphasis>
46: 366. 1980).
</paragraph>
